          <link xlink:href="uniprot:P14210"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>"Hepatocyte growth factor
http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P14210

mitogen for mature parenchymal hepatocyte cells, acts as a growth factor for a broad spectrum of tissues and cell types.


0 = HGF Absence
1 = HGF Presence"
</comment>
      </annotation>
      <nodevisualsetting x="1523" y="177" style="Input"/>
    </node>
    <node id="EGF" maxvalue="1" input="true">
      <annotation>
        <linklist>
          <link xlink:href="uniprot:P01133"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>"epidermal growth factor
http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P01133

EGF stimulates the growth of various epidermal and epithelial tissues in vivo and in vitro and of some fibroblasts in cell culture.


0 = EGF Absence
1 = EGF Presence"
</comment>
      </annotation>
      <nodevisualsetting x="1054" y="176" style="Input"/>
    </node>
    <node id="ECM" maxvalue="1" input="true">
      <annotation>
        <comment>"Extracellular matrix is the set of component  that support physically and biochemically the surrounding cells. Examples are glycoproteins

