      <value val="1">
        <exp str="RPTP_L &amp; !FAK_SRC:2 &amp; !ROS"/>
      </value>
      <annotation>
        <linklist>
          <link xlink:href="uniprot:Q15262"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>"Receptor-type tyrosine-protein phosphatase kappa
http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q15262

PTPRK is part of the Type IIb PTPR - it interacts homophilically to form dimers

0 = inactive, not expressed
1 = active, homologous RPTP binding dimer formation"
</comment>
      </annotation>
      <nodevisualsetting x="1867" y="392" style=""/>
    </node>
    <node id="RAP1" name="Ras-related protein Rap-1A/B" maxvalue="1">
      <value val="1">
        <exp str="FAK_SRC | (ECad_AJ:2 &amp; !p120_AJ)"/>
      </value>
      <annotation>
        <linklist>
          <link xlink:href="uniprot:P62834"/>
          <link xlink:href="uniprot:P61224"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>"Ras-related protein Rap-1A
http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P62834
Ras-related protein Rap-1B
http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P61224

Rap1 is predominantly involved in cell adhesion and cell junction formation.

0 = inactive
1 = activate,  guanine nucleotide-exchange factors (as C3G) "
</comment>
      </annotation>
      <nodevisualsetting x="1477" y="661" style=""/>
    </node>
    <node id="TGFBR" maxvalue="1">
      <value val="1">
        <exp str="TGFB"/>
      </value>
      <annotation>
        <linklist>
          <link xlink:href="uniprot:P36897"/>
          <link xlink:href="uniprot:P37173"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>"TGF-beta receptor type-1/2
http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P36897
http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P37173

Transmembrane serine/threonine kinase forming with the TGF-beta type II serine/threonine kinase receptor, TGFBR2, the non-promiscuous receptor for the TGF-beta cytokines TGFB1, TGFB2 and TGFB3


0 = inactive
1 = active, ligand binding, dimer formation and autophosphorylation"
</comment>
      </annotation>
      <nodevisualsetting x="797" y="447" style=""/>
    </node>
    <node id="JAK" name="Tyrosine-protein kinase JAK1/2" maxvalue="1">
      <value val="1">
        <exp str="IL6 | EGFR"/>
      </value>
      <annotation>
        <linklist>
          <link xlink:href="uniprot:P23458"/>
          <link xlink:href="uniprot:O60674"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>"Tyrosine-protein kinase JAK1
http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P23458
Tyrosine-protein kinase JAK2
http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/O60674

Tyrosine kinase of the non-receptor type, involved in the IFN-alpha/beta/gamma signal pathway OR Kinase partner for the interleukin (IL)-2 receptor. ollowing ligand-binding to cell surface receptors, phosphorylates specific tyrosine residues on the cytoplasmic tails of the receptor, creating docking sites for STATs proteins thus phosphgorylating them.

0 = inactive
1 = kinase active, phosphorylated on Tyr residues"
</comment>
      </annotation>
      <nodevisualsetting x="580" y="535" style=""/>
    </node>
    <node id="BCat" name="CTNN1" maxvalue="1">
      <value val="1">
        <exp str="!GSK3B | !BCat_AJ | HGFR"/>
      </value>
      <annotation>
        <linklist>
          <link xlink:href="uniprot:P35222"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>"Catenin beta-1
http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P35222

Cytoplasmic when it is unstabilized (high level of phosphorylation) or bound to E-Cadherin. Translocates to the nucleus when it is stabilized (low level of phosphorylation).


0 = not @ nucleus
1 = nuclear localization"
</comment>
      </annotation>
      <nodevisualsetting x="1718" y="592" style="Mesenchymal marker"/>
    </node>
    <node id="NFkB" name="Nuclear_factor_NFkappaB" maxvalue="1">
      <value val="1">
        <exp str="AKT | CSL | ROS | TGFBR"/>
      </value>
      <annotation>
        <linklist>
          <link xlink:href="uniprot:P19838"/>
          <link xlink:href="uniprot:Q00653"/>
          <link xlink:href="uniprot:Q04206"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>"Nuclear factor NF-kappa-B p105 subunit
http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P19838
Nuclear factor NF-kappa-B p100 subunit
http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q00653
Transcription factor p65
http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q04206

 NF-kappa-B is a homo- or heterodimeric complex formed by the Rel-like domain-containing proteins RELA/p65, RELB, NFKB1/p105, NFKB1/p50, REL and NFKB2/p52. NF-kappa-B complexes are held in the cytoplasm in an inactive state complexed with members of the NF-kappa-B inhibitor (I-kappa-B) family. In a conventional activation pathway, I-kappa-B is phosphorylated by I-kappa-B kinases (IKKs) in response to different activators, subsequently degraded thus liberating the active NF-kappa-B complex which translocates to the nucleus.

0 = inactive, constantly degraded
1 = active phosphorylated and subunit localized@nucleus"
</comment>
      </annotation>
      <nodevisualsetting x="1219" y="1111" style=""/>
    </node>
    <node id="SMAD" name="Mothers_against_decapentaplegic_homolog_2_4" maxvalue="1">
      <value val="1">
        <exp str="TGFBR &amp; YAP_TAZ"/>
      </value>
      <annotation>
        <linklist>
          <link xlink:href="uniprot:Q15796"/>
          <link xlink:href="uniprot:Q13485"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>"Mothers against decapentaplegic homolog 2
http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q15796
Mothers against decapentaplegic homolog 4
http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q13485

Receptor-regulated SMAD (R-SMAD) that is an intracellular signal transducer and transcriptional modulator activated by TGF-beta (transforming growth factor) and activin type 1 receptor kinases. Binds the TRE element in the promoter region of many genes that are regulated by TGF-beta and, on formation of the SMAD2/SMAD4 complex, activates transcription

0 = cytoplasmic and transcriptionally inactive
1 = active complex formation SMAD2/4 and localization @nucleus with YAP_TAZ"
</comment>
      </annotation>
      <nodevisualsetting x="798" y="641" style=""/>
    </node>
