        </linklist>
        <comment>"Recombining binding protein suppressor of hairless
http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/Q06330

 Acts as a transcriptional repressor when it is not associated with Notch proteins. When associated with some NICD product of Notch proteins (Notch intracellular domain), it acts as a transcriptional activator that activates transcription of Notch target genes.

0 = inactive
1 = active as transcription factor when bound to Notch intracellular domain"
</comment>
      </annotation>
