    <node id="ECad" name="Cadherin_1" maxvalue="1">
      <value val="1">
        <exp str="(!SNAIL | miR200) &amp; !SLUG &amp; !ZEB"/>
      </value>
      <annotation>
        <linklist>
          <link xlink:href="uniprot:P12830"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>"Cadherin-1
http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P12830

Cadherins are calcium-dependent cell adhesion proteins. They preferentially interact with themselves in a homophilic manner in connecting cells; cadherins may thus contribute to the sorting of heterogeneous cell types. Anchored to actin microfilaments through association with alpha-, beta- and gamma-catenin


0  = not expressed
1 = expressed and present in the cytoplasm"
</comment>
      </annotation>
      <nodevisualsetting x="1806" y="678" style="Epithelial marker"/>
    </node>
    <node id="ECad_AJ" name="Cadherin_1" maxvalue="2">
      <value val="2">
        <exp str="ECad &amp; BCat_AJ &amp; (RPTP | !FAK_SRC)"/>
      </value>
      <value val="1">
        <exp str="ECad &amp; !BCat_AJ &amp; (RPTP | !FAK_SRC)"/>
      </value>
      <annotation>
        <linklist>
          <link xlink:href="uniprot:P12830"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>"Cadherin-1
http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P12830

Cadherins are calcium-dependent cell adhesion proteins. They preferentially interact with themselves in a homophilic manner in connecting cells; cadherins may thus contribute to the sorting of heterogeneous cell types. Anchored to actin microfilaments through association with alpha-, beta- and gamma-catenin


0 = not @ membrane
1 = localize @ membrane together with BCat, but rapidly internalized
2 = localized @ membrane and stabilized by p120"
</comment>
      </annotation>
