    <annotation>
      <comment>v24
miR200 can interfere with  SNAIL and it's repressing activity on Ecad. There are several evidences indicating that miR200 increase ECad transcription. Added miR200--&gt;ECad
v23
chaning FAK_SRC rule for level 2 activation
v22
Adding EGFR--&gt;FAK_SRC, and changing the rules of FAK_SRC node (one activator to have level 1 and at least 2 to have level 2).
v21
v20
binary definition of CellCell_AJ, and multivalue definition of ECad_ADJ. Renaming of all the MEM nodes as ADJ. Reannotation with the new 
Updated rule of snail to avoid TGFB/SMAD overrule in EMT
v19
removed p120--|TCF_LEF, this INDUCTION (becuase of the node definition) can actually be discarded since the protein reponsible for it Kaiso, may not be sufficient enough to titrate TCF4 when just B-Cat is present, so we don't need a strong AND in the rule of TFC_LEF
v18
added SNAIL--|miR200, crucial to solve the lock between miR200 and ZEB
v17
added a ROS--&gt;FAK_SRC activation, this goes along with the fact that there is a second spike in SRC activation 45' after the adhesion in concomitance with a ROS peak. And that SRC has Cysteine residues prone to be oxidated and connected with activation.
added FAK_SRC--&gt;JNK, it is reported that FAK_SRC is fundamental for JNK activation by H2O2
v16
add the 3rd phenotypic node to sub-classify SS
removed the requirement of BCat_MEM on ECad_MEM, it is true that is needed for shuttling but we don't have a free pool of BCat to use in this, just the two localizations Cyt/MEM
v15
NFkB--&gt;SLUG (Storci et al 2010). Need a better evidence.
v14b
Model Annotation
v14
- Due to the fact that B-Cat can still be targeted for degradation maybe it make more sense to change the rule for its   nuclear activity to:
B-Cat:=!GSK3B | (!B-Cat-mem &amp; c-MET)
- change names to account for SMBL standard (no - symbol)
- remove CellCellAd--|RAP1 for p120--|RAP1 to  have CellCellAd as output node
v13
Changing the activation of RAP1, by C3G through e-cad internalization from

E-Cad-mem--&gt;RAP1 to E-Cad--&gt;RAP1

this means that  the lack of E-Cad at the membrane, while there is still production of it, implies  higher internalization and thus activation of RAP1
As before the enstablishment of strong cadherin based interaction blocks this activation.

v12
Added B-Cad-mem--&gt;E-Cad-mem to account for the fact that B-Cat may work as a shuttle for proper localization of E.Cad at the membrane</comment>
